  "server": {
    "name": "io.nyc.bklynlibrary",
    "title": "Brooklyn Public Library (BPL)",
    "version": "0.1.0",
    "description": "Agent-native access to Brooklyn Public Library \u2014 branches, events and programs, digital collections, and licensed electronic resources (from BPL's public Drupal JSON:API), plus catalog search and item availability (from the BiblioCommons ILS), and the net-new ability to apply for a library card and place a hold on a book that today live only behind vendor logins.",
    "instructions": "Use find_branches / get_branch to locate library branches by holds-pickup, region, hours, or free text. find_events searches programs and story times (registration workflow included). search_catalog / get_catalog_item query the BiblioCommons bibliographic catalog and availability. find_digital_collections covers digitized assets, feature collections, and archival finding aids; find_electronic_resources lists licensed databases. get_my_library_card and list_my_holds require an authenticated patron. apply_for_library_card and place_hold (net-new) mutate state \u2014 confirm the item, pickup branch, and patron details with the user before submitting. Note: BPL is one of three separate NYC library systems (NYPL, BPL, Queens); this server covers BPL only."
  },
